        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 1:29PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 129 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hot Springs National Park, or near Hot Springs, moving south at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hot Springs...                    Mountain Pine...
Hot Springs Memorial Field...     Hot Springs National Park...
Lofton...                         Rockwell...
Red Oak...                        Oaklawn Racetrack...
Pettyview...                      Sunshine...
Hempwallace...                    Royal...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
